                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3318: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-23T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 23 [<hi rend="italic">24?</hi>], 1931—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 24—7:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1127. Your 469, December 23, 5 p.m.<note n="5" xml:id="d654fn5">Not
                        printed.</note> I have just been informed by telephone from Tientsin that
                    the commander of the U. S. Fifteenth Infantry there has been informed by the
                    Japanese military of their intention to land at Tientsin 1,700 troops, including
                    a company of artillery, on December 26–27 for precautionary purposes. We have no
                    evidence at present of any disturbance there to cause this Japanese action.
                    Tientsin and the whole region between it and Chinchow are peaceful. I can
                    therefore conceive of no reason for the Japanese action except an intended
                    attack toward Chinchow and possible disorders caused thereby at Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
